hs%20after%20the%20FTC%20delayed%20its%20new%20click-to-cancel%20rule%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20working%20late%20on%20her%20laptop%2C%20burning%20out%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6821fcf8c6ad288d1480a1f7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EYour%20unwanted%20subscriptions%20were%20supposed%20to%20get%20easier%20to%20cancel%20until%20the%20FTC%20delayed%20the%20enforcement%20of%20its%20new%20rule.%3Cp%3EYana%20Iskayeva%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EUnwanted%20subscriptions%20were%20about%20to%20get%20easier%20to%20cancel%20with%20the%20FTC's%20new%20click-to-cancel%20rule.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20the%20commission%20just%20delayed%20its%20enforcement%20deadline%20by%20two%20more%20months.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEx-FTC%20commissioner%20Lina%20Khan%20says%20the%20move%20lets%20firms%20%26quot%3Bkeep%20trapping%20people%26quot%3B%20in%20pesky%20subscriptions.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20about%20to%20get%20easier%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20that%20pesky%20subscription%20you've%20been%20stuck%20paying%20for%20until%20the%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission%20delayed%20enforcement%20of%20its%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fftc-cancel-subscriptions-rule-click-to-cancel-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eclick-to-cancel%3C%2Fa%3E%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFormer%20FTC%20chair%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fftc-chair-lina-khan-antitrust-critic-big-tech-amazon-2021-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ELina%20Khan%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20a%20Thursday%20post%20on%20X%2C%20said%20that%20the%20enforcement%20delay%20will%20give%20firms%20more%20time%20%26quot%3Bto%20keep%20trapping%20people%20in%20subscriptions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20consumers%20are%20familiar%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-subscriptions-nightmare-recurring-payments-cancellation-company-tricks-trap-customers-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eunwanted%20subscription%3C%2Fa%3E%20rigamarole%3A%20It's%20painlessly%20simple%20to%20sign%20up%20online%20for%20a%20streaming%20service%2C%20gym%2C%20or%20other%20subscription%2C%20but%20when%20the%20time%20comes%20to%20stop%20monthly%20payments%20and%20unsubscribe%2C%20there's%20no%20way%20to%20do%20it%20digitally%2C%20and%20you're%20forced%20into%20the%20dreaded%20routine%20of%20navigating%20call%20center%20chatbots%20that%20only%20seem%20to%20operate%20during%20the%20middle%20of%20your%20workday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FTC's%20click-to-cancel%20rule%20was%20supposed%20to%20go%20into%20effect%20in%20its%20entirety%20this%20week%2C%20ending%20the%20nightmarish%20cycle%20and%20making%20it%20just%20as%20easy%20for%20consumers%20to%20cancel%20their%20subscriptions%20as%20it%20was%20to%20start%20them.%20But%20on%20Friday%2C%20the%20commission's%20leaders%20voted%20to%20extend%20its%20enforcement%20deadline%20by%20two%20more%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHaving%20conducted%20a%20fresh%20assessment%20of%20the%20burdens%20that%20forcing%20compliance%20by%20this%20date%20would%20impose%2C%20the%20Commission%20has%20determined%20that%20the%20original%20deferral%20period%20insufficiently%20accounted%20for%20the%20complexity%20of%20compliance%2C%26quot%3B%20read%20a%20statement%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fandrew-ferguson-new-chairman-federal-trade-commission-antitrust-big-tech-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EChairman%20Andrew%20Ferguson%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20co-signed%20by%20commissioners%20Melissa%20Holyoak%20and%20Mark%20Meador%2C%20about%20the%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20FTC%20approved%20the%20click-to-cancel%20rule%2C%20also%20known%20as%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalregister.gov%2Fdocuments%2F2024%2F11%2F15%2F2024-25534%2Fnegative-option-rule%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENegative%20Option%20Rule%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20November%202024%2C%20businesses%20had%20more%20than%20six%20months%20to%20comply%20before%20enforcement%20was%20scheduled%20to%20begin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rule's%20requirement%20to%20remove%20statements%20that%20misrepresent%20the%20nature%20of%20a%20subscription%20took%20effect%20on%20January%2014.%20Its%20enforcement%20provisions%20%E2%80%94%20requiring%20clear%20disclosures%2C%20user%20consent%2C%20and%20easy%20cancellation%20policies%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%20were%20set%20to%20take%20effect%20on%20May%2014.%20However%2C%20the%20FTC's%20latest%20decision%20pushes%20the%20enforcement%20deadline%20back%20by%2060%20days%2C%20to%20July%2014.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20object%20to%20the%20delay%2C%26quot%3B%20former%20FTC%20commissioners%20Alvaro%20Bedoya%20and%20Rebecca%20Slaughter%20said%20in%20a%20joint%20statement%20posted%20to%20social%20media%20on%20Tuesday.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20were%20we%20allowed%20to%20exercise%20our%20duties%20as%20commissioners%2C%20we%20would%20have%20voted%20'no.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBedoya%20and%20Slaughter%20were%20the%20only%20two%20Democrats%20serving%20as%20FTC%20commissioners%20until%C2%A0March%2018%2C%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewhen%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20fired%20them.%20The%20pair%2C%20whose%20terminations%20indicated%20their%20service%20at%20the%20FTC%20was%20%26quot%3Binconsistent%26quot%3B%20with%20Trump's%20policy%20priorities%2C%20have%20filed%20suit%20against%20the%20administration%2C%20alleging%20their%20firings%20violate%20a%201935%20Supreme%20Court%20precedent%20that%20the%20president%20cannot%20fire%20FTC%20commissioners%20without%20cause%2C%20CNN%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20Bedoya%20and%20Slaughter%20had%20remained%20at%20the%20FTC%2C%20the%20conservative%20majority%20at%20the%20commission%20would%20be%20able%20to%20pass%20rules%20via%20a%203-2%20vote.%20The%20decision%20to%20delay%20the%20click-to-cancel%20enforcement%20received%20a%203-0%20vote%2C%20with%20all%20three%20Republican%20commissioners%20voting%20in%20favor%20of%20the%20deadline%20extension.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20companies%20create%20these%20traps%2C%26quot%3B%20Bedoya%20and%20Slaughter's%20statement%20continued.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20the%20ones%20who%20made%20it%20so%20hard%20to%20get%20out.%20They%20didn't%20have%20to%20wait%20to%20make%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcancel-subscriptions-congress-ftc-dark-practices-autorenewal-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eeasier%20to%20unsubscribe%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20they%20did%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0they%20waited%20until%20the%20FTC%20told%20them%20to%20stop.%20Then%2C%20they%20%3Cem%3Estill%20%3C%2Fem%3Egot%20six%20months%20to%20get%20their%20houses%20in%20order.%20Why%20do%20they%20get%20another%20two%20months%20to%20comply%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepresentatives%20for%20the%20FTC%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funwanted-subscriptions-extended-ftc-delays-enforcement-click-cancel-rule-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1747353619000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6826526068a29290080178e6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funwanted-subscriptions-extended-ftc-delays-enforcement-click-cancel-rule-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20FTC%20has%20delayed%20enforcement%20of%20its%20new%20click-to-cancel%20rule%2C%20which%20aimed%20to%20make%20it%20easier%20for%20consumers%20to%20end%20unwanted%20subscriptions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ktangalakislippert%40businessinsider.com%20(Katherine%20Tangalakis-Lippert)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A21%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funwanted-subscriptions-extended-ftc-d