able%20than%20the%20Silk%20%26amp%3B%20Snow%20Knitted%20Weighted%20Blanket.%20As%20I%20mentioned%20in%20the%20design%20section%2C%20the%20Cotton%20Napper%20has%20a%20tighter%20knit%20with%20smaller%20cotton%20fabric.%20I%20preferred%20this%20feel%2C%20as%20it%20kept%20my%20temperature%20regulated%20and%20provided%20even%20weight%20across%20my%20body.%20The%20weight%20distribution%20felt%20less%20even%20with%20the%20Silk%20%26amp%3B%20Snow%20Knitted%20Weighted%20Blanket%2C%20since%20there%20were%20more%20empty%20spaces%20in%20the%20blanket%20weave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20large%20holes%20in%20the%20Silk%20%26amp%3B%20Snow%20blanket%20also%20aggravated%20one%20of%20the%20few%20downsides%20of%20knit%20weighted%20blankets%3A%20my%20toes%20and%20fingers%20got%20stuck%20in%20the%20knit%20as%20I%20used%20the%20blanket.%20This%20happened%20with%20the%20Bearaby%20Cotton%20Napper%2C%20too%2C%20but%20the%20smaller%20weave%20meant%20it%20was%20less%20prevalent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bce638e7-7fd7-461e-857f-138fa1db0d8b%5C%22%3EBearaby%20vs%20Silk%20%26amp%3B%20Snow%3A%20Care%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Cotton%20Napper%20and%20Knitted%20Weighted%20Blanket%20are%20both%20technically%20machine%20washable%2C%20but%20be%20sure%20to%20check%20your%20washer%20to%20ensure%20it%20can%20support%20their%20weight.%20Both%20brands%20recommend%20washing%20the%20blanket%20in%20cold%20water%20and%20tumble%20drying%20on%20low.%20For%20instance%2C%20Bearaby%20recommends%20taking%20blankets%2020%20pounds%20and%20heavier%20to%20a%20commercial%20laundromat.%20Also%2C%20be%20careful%20not%20to%20hang%20either%20blanket%20to%20dry%20since%20it%20will%20stretch%20the%20loops.%20Silk%20%26amp%3B%20Snow%20notes%20that%20their%20blankets%20should%20not%20be%20cared%20for%20in%20top%20loading%20washers%20and%20dryers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20more%20information%20on%20caring%20for%20your%20weighted%20blanket%2C%20see%20our%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fg